  "texts": [
    "The theory is called Orchestrated Objective Reduction (Orch-OR) and was first introduced in 1995.",
    "All these years it saw many critics arguing about its validity.",
    "However, experimental data collected from patients under sedation whose brain activity was recorded via electroencephalogram (EEG), showed that there is a solid basis of what the two scientists proposed, even though much of the existing skepticism remains up to our days [28].",
    "As a side note and provided that Orch OR is the case with consciousness, we would like to introduce a purely philosophical Goedel Expansion.",
    "Could there be another entity that controls our perception of self, via quantum entanglement of these microstates?"
  ],
